shared_text:
Shelton High School Activities
July 24 at 11:28 PM ·

Thank you to all of the athletes and coaches that took time out of their evening to clean up the grounds at Shelton Public Schools. Our goal is to always create a culture worth fighting for. We want to invest in one another to the point that everyone wants to fight for the culture and for each other. Investing personal time and work in to who and what you represent should bring a sense of pride and accomplishment and ultimately a desire to fight for the culture you have worked so hard for. Strong cultures will ultimately lead to our student-athletes successes both on and off the field. Yesterday we took another step toward building that culture.

Shoutouts to Angel, Sam, Jamesyn, Will S, Will R, Addison, Callee, Makeda, Harper, Drake, Emmi, Kiersten, Alia, Bri S, Dru, Kenna, Ashton, Xavier, Christian, Tyson, Mason, Zach, Mayte, Emily B, Jalyn, Halie, Matthew, Coby, Coach Walter, Coach Kropp and her husband Pete, Coach Horak, Mr. Kenton, Coaches Jeff and Amanda Thober, and Coach Province.

Investing personal time and work in to who and what you represent should bring a sense of pride and accomplishment and ultimately a desire to fight for the culture you have worked so hard for. post_text:
Shelton Student-Athletes,

If you are planning to participate in ANY sport next year, and want to raise the level of your game, the weight room is the place to be this summer. The weight room will open up next Monday, June 1st. Please see the attached 2020 Summer Strength schedule to see start times for each group, look over the weight room waiver you and your parent/guardian will be required to sign and bring back Wednesday, June 3rd (you will also be given paper copies on Monday), and come next week ready to mold yourself in to a better student-athlete.

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Mrs. Thober or any of your respective coaches. We are all excited to see you and work with you this summer...within CDC guidelines, of course.

Go Dawgs!

Shelton FFA Chapter
April 5 at 6:55 PM ·

Spring Plant Sales! We have a wide selection of vegetable plants and flowers available for sale! All proceeds will support the greenhouse funds and the Shelton FFA Chapter.

In light of our current situation, this year's sales will be online. Please use the google form link below to place your order. To see the plants available in more detail - check out the detailed list of plants link. After you place an order, you will be contacted to arrange an individual pick-up time to limit the number of people in the greenhouse area. All payments need to be by check or cash.

All orders will be on a first-come-first-serve basis - the order form is time stamped. If we run out of a plant that you requested, you will be contacted.

Detailed list of Plants: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vQU31CNm2sPj8z7XbBeXWnzQawvda_EuUDp8EBrrXrRs_5vGB1ItlzrXH9eLGRG6kXva8Z0BbH2FqnF/pub?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000

post_text: Congratulations Wyatt!
shared_text:
Shelton FFA Chapter
April 3 at 12:37 PM ·

Had the state convention taken place today as planned, our senior FFA member Wyatt Ohlman would have walked across the stage to earn his State FFA Degree. The State FFA Degree is the highest degree the state association can bestow upon a member. Each year members are awarded the degree based upon their comprehensive Supervised Agricultural Experience Program. FFA members must submit two years of SAE record books, meet all minimum qualifications as well as completing an interview to be awarded the State FFA Degree. Wyatt's SAE program included an entrepreneurship project focused around Team Roping, and a placement project working for local feedlots. Congratulations Wyatt!

Updated March 20, 2020

Students, families, and staff,

Due to the continuing safety concerns from the coronavirus pandemic, the Shelton Public Schools will remain closed until April 5th. At that time the district, with recommendations from state and federal authorities, will determine if it’s safe to resume classes again. Please remember online classes for third through twelfth grade students begin on Monday, March 23rd. Pre-K, first, and second grade parents may drop off and pick up new packets in the main entrance breezeway on Friday, March 27th from 7:00am to 5:00pm.

Shelton FFA Chapter
March 3 at 1:24 AM ·

Congratulations to FFA member Jacob S.
Over the weekend his proficiency award application in Grain Production was awarded a gold rating, and selected as a top 3 finalist for the state!
Jacob will now proceed to the State Convention where he will interview with industry professionals to determine the winner between the three finalists.

BWC Reward Tier 3 Update:

Congratulations to our Qualifiers:
Kesleigh P., Ella K., Kylie R., Alison N., Gabby W., Jackson T., Giles J., Ian K., Michael R., Wyatt R., LeTavion D., Owen S., Ava R., Brooklynn P., Griffin W., Jackson G., Jazmyne M., Chanze M., Grace W., Gracie W., Shelby M., Sonja W., Charles F., Erin G., Macy W., Matthew G., Susie C.!!!

This is the most students we have had qualify in the four years we have done it! Looking forward to our visit next Tuesday at the Viaero Event Center in Kearney!

All students will be getting their permission slips today. Please have them signed and back to Mr. Walter as soon as possible, but absolutely before we leave.

#BWC #BulldogPride #HealthyStart #PositiveCommunity #Walk2Skate #LetsGo
